Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450}(into 2cm slices, then into 2cm wide chips) (no need to peel). Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and discard the core and seeds, sliced into thin strips, chopped into 1cm pieces). Trim the @spring onion{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Bash the @black peppercorns{1%sachet} with the back of a pan until crushed.

Pop the chips on a #large, low sided, wide baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two #baking trays{} if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into a #large bowl{} and season with salt and pepper, mix. Add the @cornflour{50%g}, @ground ginger{1%tsp}, @water{5000%ml}(for the chicken), @soy sauce{12.5%ml} to another large bowl. Season with salt and pepper and whisk until well combined. Heat approx 1-2cm of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

> You want the oil to be nice and hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

While the oil gets hot, add the @British chicken thighs{4} in the cornflour mixture so all pieces are completely covered. Then, dip it in the breadcrumbs to coat on both sides. Pop on a #plate{}, repeat with the rest.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once the oil is hot, carefully lay the chicken in the pan and fry until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

> TIP: Careful not to burn yourself on the hot oil, turn the heat down if the chicken is burning.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pop the chicken on one end of a large #baking tray{} and place the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} on the other end. Drizzle a little oil over the tenderstem and season with salt and pepper. When your chips are halfway through cooking, place the chicken tray onto the middle shelf of the oven until everything is cooked, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Carefully set the hot oil aside, dispose once cool. Pop another frying pan onto a medium high heat with a drizzle of oil. When hot, add the bell pepper and stir fry until slightly charred, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt, add the garlic, spring onion, @Chinese five spice{1%tsp} and crushed peppercorns. Stir and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Once the chips are cooked, remove them from oven and add the pepper mixture to the tray, mix everything together.

Serve the chicken with the salt and pepper chips and broccoli on the side. Pop the @Szechuan paste{50%g} into a little #bowl{} for dipping and enjoy!